journals.notes:
As a point of learning I am curious about my code vs the code that was implimented.
This: 
<pre>
 let hasGeom = false;
        if (viewScreen === 'kers') {
            noGeom = Object.values(kers)
                .filter((ker) => !empty(ker.exceptions));
            noGeom.forEach((exceptionIndex) => (exceptionIndex.exceptions.forEach((exception) => {
                if (exception.geom !== null) {
                    hasGeom = true;
                }
            })
            ));
        }
</pre>
VS this:
<pre>

/**
         * Function to check if geom is populated on each exception.
         *
         * @param {object} theKers - Get the Kers Object.
         * @returns {object} Returns a filtered object of exceptions with geom.
         */
        const generateAnArrayOfOnlyGeom = (theKers) => (
            Object.values(theKers)
                .filter((ker) => !ker.passed)
                .map((ker) => ker.exceptions.filter((exception) => exception.geom))
                .join('')
        );
        const hasGeom = generateAnArrayOfOnlyGeom(kers) || false;
</pre>

